Writing User Stories:

As a user,
So that I can browse available links
I would like links stored in a list.

As a user,
So that I can remember find sites I have recently bookmarked,
I would like to be able see new links to my bookmark manager. (DESCENDING CHRONOLOGICAL)

As a user,
So that I can remember interesting sites,
I would like to be able add new links with the site's address and title to my bookmark manager

As a user,
So that I can categories my links,
I would like to be able to add tags to bookmarks.

As a user,
So I can find links I am interested in,
I would like to be able to filter my links according to their tags.




WHAT IS PERSISTENCE? Persistence is the layer in which you store your data.

What are the four main design approaches regarding data storage?

Pure in-memory, no persistence at all.
In memory with periodic snapshots (redis)
disk-based with update in place writes, such as MySQL or MongoDB
Commit-Log Based (oldschool) SQL Server/Oracle.
